# 6. きらきら光る道しるべ

Saki: ♪—————
Saki: Ugh... This isn't right either...
Saki: But I still want to contribute to our music somehow. I want to be able to do more for us.
Saki: So please, let me keep doing this for a little while longer! I promise to be super careful about not overworking myself too!
Saki: (Even though I told Shiho that, this might actually be too much for me...)
Rin: Heya♪
Saki: Rin!
Rin: Are you having a solo session, Sakki? You're such a hard-working girl♪
Saki: Uh... Yeah! I've been working on something and...
Rin: Oh, are you working on that original Leo/need song you were talking about?!
Saki: I am. But...
Saki: I've hit a block and was actually just thinking about going home...
Rin: What? You're leaving?
Saki: Yeah...
Rin: Wait, Sakki...! Before you go, can I play something for you?!
Saki: You're gonna play something for me, Rin?
Saki: Sure, of course... But which instrument?
Rin: On your synth, silly! Okay, here we go☆
Saki: R-Right!
Rin: ♪——...
Saki: Wait, is Rin singing too...?
Saki: (Oh, is she improvising as she goes...?)
Rin: ♪—————　♪——...
Saki: Hehe...
Saki: (But this melody's sort of all over the place, she did a really weird key change just now and her chord progression doesn't sound right either...)
Saki: (But at the same time, why?)
Saki: (It sounds so fun and exciting...!)
Rin: Hehehe. How was that, Sakki?!
Saki: You're amazing, Rin! That was so much fun!
Rin: Really?! Yay! I'm glad you liked it so much, Sakki♪
Saki: Um, Rin? Did you write that yourself?
Rin: Huh? No, I didn't write anything.
Saki: What? But that song...
Rin: Haha. That was just something I wanted to try and sing along to!
Saki: Sing along...?
Saki: Wait, hang on...! Can you at least tell me what was going through your mind while you were singing just now?
Rin: Hmm... Well... I wasn't really thinking about anything at all♪
Saki: What?!
Rin: You seemed a little down, Sakki...
Rin: So I decided to play this song to try and cheer you up.
Saki: You were trying to cheer me up...?
Rin: I'm not really sure how to describe it, but you can't make a song you're playing sparkle unless you really mean it.
Saki: Unless I mean it...?
Saki: (Oh, right...)
Saki: (It sounded like a mess, but it felt like fun because Rin genuinely wanted me to feel better.)
Saki: (But in my case...)
Saki: (I've been so focused on helping everyone out by coming up with a song that suits our band, so I'd forgotten about what I want it to convey...)
Saki: (What thoughts are going into this song...?)
Saki: (What do I want it to convey...?)
Rin: Is everything okay, Sakki?
Saki: Yeah...! Thanks, Rin.
Saki: I'm still not exactly sure what kind of song it's gonna be, but I think I'm starting to get a better idea!
Rin: Really?! That's great!
Rin: You can do it, Sakki! I know your song's gonna be really amazing♪
Saki: Thanks!!
